subtitleNullable: The ticket sales to Toronto Island from 2015
descriptionNullable:
The Toronto Islands are a chain of 15 small islands in Lake Ontario, south of mainland Toronto, Ontario, Canada.

Ferries to [Toronto Island Park](https://toronto-islands.ca/) operate year-round out of Jack Layton Ferry Terminal. Ferries carry passengers to and from Centre Island, Hanlan’s Point and Ward’s Island. There are limited amenities during the off-season.

This dataset provides near real-time information on ferry ticket sales and ticket redemptions. The counts are provided in 15 minute intervals and are updated hourly. They encompass all product types and include both online and POS-kiosk sales.

For additional information about Toronto Island Park or the ferry service, please visit toronto.ca/parks or contact parks@toronto.ca.

Column Description: 

_id -- Unique row identifier for Open Data database

Timestamp -- The 15 minute interval (end time) that the data represents

Redemption Count -- The ticket redemption count between the previous and current timestamp

Sales Count -- The ticket sales count between the previous and current timestamp
